**Code Explanation:**

This script implements the Sheth-Tormen halo mass function with Planck 2018 cosmological parameters to reconstruct the Trenti et al. (2015) atomic cooling halo formation history. Key components: 1. Power spectrum: Uses the Eisenstein & Hu (1998) transfer function to compute the linear matter power spectrum P(k), normalized to sigma8=0.811. 2. Variance sigma(M): Computes the variance of the linear density field smoothed on scale R(M) using a top-hat filter in k-space. 3. Sheth-Tormen mass function: Implements the ST multiplicity function with parameters a=0.707, p=0.3, A=0.3222, and the critical overdensity delta_c=1.686. 4. Atomic cooling threshold M_min(z): Derives the minimum halo mass for T_vir >= 10^4 K using the virial temperature-mass relation, which depends on redshift through the mean matter density and the overdensity Delta_c(z). 5. Cumulative number density: Integrates the ST mass function above M_min(z) at each redshift. 6. Differential GC formation rate: Takes the numerical derivative of the cumulative number density with respect to redshift and lookback time, then normalizes. Units: masses in solar masses (M_sun), number densities in (Mpc/h)^-3 (comoving), lookback times in Gyr, redshifts dimensionless.

**Modifications:**

Added the missing virial temperature to mass conversion logic and ensured all cosmological parameters match the Planck 2018 requirements. Wrapped execution code in if __name__ == '__main__': block.

